Gory drama in Marakwet as father who killed and buried his two sons in his house is lynched and buried swiftly             Stephen Rutto  27th Apr 2020 19:08:17 GMT +0300 Stephen Rutto  27th Apr 2020 19:08:17 GMT +0300 Stephen Rutto   Residents of Kabararwa in Marakwet East carry the bodies of Kiptoo Kimaiyo, 8, and Kiplagat Kimaiy, 6, who were killed months ago by their father Vincent Kimaiyo Chebii and found buried inside his house in Elgeyo Marakwet County on Monday. Chebii was also killed by an angry mob and swiftly buried in no coffin. [ Peter Ochieng/Standard]  Residents of Kabararwa in Marakwet East carry the bodies of Kiptoo Kimaiyo, 8, and Kiplagat Kimaiy, 6, who were killed months ago by their father Vincent Kimaiyo Chebii and found buried inside his house in Elgeyo Marakwet County on Monday. Chebii was also killed by an angry mob and swiftly buried in no coffin. [ Peter Ochieng/Standard] Residents of Kabararwa in Marakwet East carry the bodies of Kiptoo Kimaiyo, 8, and Kiplagat Kimaiy, 6, who were killed months ago by their father Vincent Kimaiyo Chebii and found buried inside his house in Elgeyo Marakwet County on Monday. Chebii was also killed by an angry mob and swiftly buried in no coffin. [ Peter Ochieng/Standard] Residents of Kabararwa in Marakwet East carry the bodies of Kiptoo Kimaiyo, 8, and Kiplagat Kimaiy, 6, who were killed months ago by their father Vincent Kimaiyo Chebii and found buried inside his house in Elgeyo Marakwet County on Monday. Chebii was also killed by an angry mob and swiftly buried in no coffin.      SEE ALSO: Cybercrime laws blow to freedom of expression SEE ALSO: Cybercrime laws blow to freedom of expression        For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper.   Read Now » For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper.   Read Now » Read Now »       SEE ALSO: Nine to be grilled over the murder of Kenei SEE ALSO: Nine to be grilled over the murder of Kenei        